phrases: Mom wants you to come say goodbye to Dad.
This is the last chance you will have to physically touch him.
Please take the time to do so.
Why do not you wash it?
If you just pour it from the top, Dad's going to get cold.
There is a letter for you.
What was I supposed to do?
I have not really heard from her.
Do not tell me you two got in a fight.
No, it is not like that...
Did you eat a dark plant?
Who would eat something like that?!
You are the one who is creeping me out!
What the hell did you do to your hair?
I thought I was getting a little old for pigtails.
Do not you think, my dear senior?
Hearing you talk like that makes my skin crawl.
You cannot just grab on to it as you please.
This is totally out of left field!
I spent a lot of time thinking after what happened...
Like about Master... I mean, Takanashi.
Hey, Tsuyuri, is your eye all right?
My goodness, she does look rather strange.
Little slow on the uptake, are not we?
Please do not call me that.
Do you want to see my eye?
Anyway, what is with the Rikka impression?
from the wielder of the Wicked Eye.
On the final eve of the new moon, I was entrusted with the full measure of that dark power.
In other words, I am the Wicked Eye's successor.
Does that thing really need a successor?!
The Wicked Eye must live on.
So long as the Dark Flame Master draws breath.
Wow, that sounds so... deathly cool!
And whose side are you supposed to be on?
Well, that did not take long to clean up.
Looking back at it, we really were not doing much.
By the way, how was the Drama Club?
Oh, I went to check it out.
They were like, we will do things no one has ever done before!
And we will pave the way for a new age!.
I mean, I have no problem with enthusiasm.
It is just... this really seemed like a case of eighth-grader syndrome to me.
I got the impression they felt like they were different to other people.
Like they were special because they could see something others could not.
It felt like they were a bit full of themselves, you know?
I mean, remember how we both wanted to put our eighth-grader syndrome behind us
and just be normal high schoolers once we got here?
But I think we were just caught up in our own ideas of what a normal high schooler should be.
What are you trying to say?
Just that maybe everyone always has some kind of syndrome, you know?
Oh, do not worry about it.
I do not want you to break any more of them.
I do not break them that much, do I?
I understand you are sad because Takanashi's gone, but...
You mean you do not know?
The movers came in the evening, and...
You said you would come back.
You said you would be right back!
I do not think you can make it at this hour.
The train you need does not run this late.
Mom, Grandpa, and Grandma all looked so happy.
They were so relieved when I said that I would do it.
So I think I made the right choice.
I told her to take off her eyepatch...
and leave her eighth-grader syndrome behind.
When you read this letter, you may no longer be the Dark Flame Master.
Because in 2012, as per the Mayan prophecy,
the world will be devastated by wave of destruction, weakening your mental energy.
You may have attained enlightenment and abandoned your destiny,
reducing yourself to a pathetic commoner, content simply to enjoy life.
I sense that this is the case.
That is why I have written you this letter.
Do not be fooled, Dark Flame Master.
You were chosen by the Dark Lord.
I wrote this to myself in two years when I was in eighth grade.
It is just a token from one of the local arcades.
It does not have any special powers.
Not that I mind, but where are you going in the middle of the night?
I am going to go get Rikka.
This is not what I wanted.
This is not what I wanted to say or do for her.
I, wielder of the Second Wicked Eye, bear a message for you.
It did not feel like it had really happened.
In fact, I could not feel anything at all.
Because I thought he would get better for sure.
I thought that until the morning he passed away.
That is when I met Yuuta.
I mean, the Wicked Eye found you two years ago.
When she went to the Priestess's place.
Grandpa said we can live with them.
Then what will happen to our place?
The air drips heavy with malice.
I watched him every day since then.
I sense that I am being watched.
Rikka thought it was wonderful that you could think like that.
She thought you were so much cooler than she was because you were true to yourself.
Rikka is a girl who was saved by her eighth-grader syndrome.
From the moment she laid eyes on you, she came to admire it.
She was bewitched by your power and tried to follow you in your footsteps.
That is why she came to you!
It could not have been anyone else!
Oh, I need to water the plants.
No, wielder of the Wicked Eye!
I have something I must show you.
What the hell are you doing up there?
Are you satisfied with this boring reality?
Or will you choose to rewrite it with me?
What are you doing up there?
It is not what it looks like!
Come on, do your part already!
I am going to feel you all over!
It is not what it looks like!
We asked Deko to give us a ride.
With the Dark Flame Master's power... this is... nothing!
But those are just cruise liners.
This is the power of darkness.
The true feelings you have been holding back.
People always say they feel awkward about having eighth-grader syndrome.
They say that they do not want to talk about it, that they want to forget about it for good.
But does that really get rid of our crazy old selves and their wild fantasies...
back when we thought we were special, when we thought something greater watched over us?
People sometimes tell lies, imagine a completely different fantasy world, dream about the distant future,
or invent a lover's relationship that only exists inside their heads.
This process repeats from the day we are born until the day we die.
But it is dear to us.
It is an illness known as self-consciousness.
It is something we must all face known as ourselves.
Indeed, we carry our eighth-grader syndrome throughout all of our lives.
Do you want to see my eye?
But to be honest, it is an embarrassing thing to have.
